{"lemma":"جُمْجُمَةٌ","slug":"جُمْجُمَةٌ","root":"ج.م.ج.م","root_slug":"ج-م-ج-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-م-ج-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6236"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8F%D9%85%D9%92%D8%AC%D9%8F%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"skull, cranium"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Golgotha (biblical): The hill outside Jerusalem where Jesus is reported to have been crucified."}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Aramaic גּוּלְגַּלְתָּא (gulgaltā), Hebrew גֻּלְגֹּלֶת (gulgṓleṯ), Akkadian 𒄢𒄢𒇻 (gulgullu), Egyptian DA-DA-tp:Z1 (ḏꜣḏꜣ, “head”)."},"ipa":["/d͡ʒum.d͡ʒu.ma/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6236","headword_ar":"جُمْجُمَةٌ","root":"jm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skull;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bone that contains the brain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K: *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiHofN","text_ar":"قِحْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bone above the brain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a separate portion of the skull,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a distinct bone of the skull"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bones of the head;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, Mgh, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all of them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the uppermost of them being the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAmap","text_ar":"هَامَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAar, TA;) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hAmp","text_ar":"هامة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jmjmp","text_ar":"جمجمة"},{"kind":"text","text":"altogether; (ISh, TA;) and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qHf","text_ar":"قحف"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to be a piece of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jmjmp","text_ar":"جمجمة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jumojumN","text_ar":"جُمْجُمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [or this (in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamojamN","text_ar":"جَمْجَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") is a coll. gen. n.,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamaAjimu","text_ar":"جَمَاجِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is the pl. properly so called, and that which is more commonly known]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Sometimes it is used to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so that one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*uwA mino kul~i jumojumapK dirohamFA","text_ar":"خُذُوا مِنْ كُلِّ جُمْجُمَةٍ دِرْهَمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take ye from every man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head, a dirhem"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; like as one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino kul~i raA^osK","text_ar":"مِنْ كُلِّ رَاْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waDaEa AlA_imaAmu","text_ar":"وَضَعَ الاـِمَامُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaraAja EalaY AljamaAjimi EalaY kul~i jumojumapK ka*aA","text_ar":"الخَرَاجَ عَلَى الجَمَاجِمِ عَلَى كُلِّ جُمْجُمَةٍ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Imám imposed the tax,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land-tax, upon the heads; upon every head so much"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wooden bowl:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bowl of glass;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiHofN","text_ar":"قِحْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Az, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of measure for corn or the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b5-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Chiefs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lords,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the Arabs; because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jmjmp","text_ar":"جمجمة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the head, which is the most noble of the members: (TA:) also, (TA,) [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamaAjimu","text_ar":"جَمَاجِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has this meaning. (T, K, TA.) And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any sons of a father that are persons of might,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power, and eminence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA:) and [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamaAjimu","text_ar":"جَمَاجِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tribes"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaAy^il","text_ar":"قَبَايِل"},{"kind":"text","text":") of the Arabs"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which comprise"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buTuwn","text_ar":"بُطُون"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in relation to which persons are called;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as Kelb Ibn-Webreh; for when you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobiY~N","text_ar":"كَلْبِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", you do not need to call the person in relation to any of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bTwn","text_ar":"بطون"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tribes"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qbAy^l","text_ar":"قبايل"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in relation to which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bTwn","text_ar":"بطون"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are called;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jimaAmN","text_ar":"جِمَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well that is dug in salt ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sixty head of camels."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IF, IB, TA.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamaAjimu AlHaArivi","text_ar":"جَمَاجِمُ الحَارِثِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The piece of wood at the head of which is the ploughshare."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Msb","S","T"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}